HEADWORD: High-wrought
<hw>High"-wrought`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Wrought with fine art or skill; elaborate.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Pope.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Worked up, or swollen, to a high degree; <as>as, a
